WEBVTT

00:02.105 --> 00:04.850
<i>Hey, it's Jon. Do me a favor.
Love each other.</i>

00:04.875 --> 00:06.686
<i>... our world came crashing down.</i>

00:06.710 --> 00:08.321
[VOICE BREAKING] What is this?

00:08.345 --> 00:10.557
You spoke at his funeral!

00:10.581 --> 00:12.258
I trusted you!

00:12.282 --> 00:13.393
[SOPHIE YELLS]

00:13.417 --> 00:15.085
- <i>But somehow...</i>
- This is for you.

00:15.110 --> 00:16.367
<i>... we found ways to heal...</i>

00:16.392 --> 00:19.218
- Finally did it. I quit my job!
- <i>... to move on...</i>

00:19.243 --> 00:21.467
It doesn't have to mean anything.
Just have some fun.

00:21.492 --> 00:22.492
<i>... to find ourselves.</i>

00:22.517 --> 00:24.237
Of course I'm still
interested in the fellowship.

00:24.261 --> 00:25.271
I would love to do it.

00:25.295 --> 00:26.639
Your Aunt Lindsay's an alcoholic,

00:26.663 --> 00:28.608
and I have the same problem.

00:28.632 --> 00:30.810
Since I've been sober,
I've been thinking a lot.

00:30.834 --> 00:31.913
Do you remember the lake house?

00:31.937 --> 00:33.480
You ever wonder why we stopped going?

00:33.504 --> 00:34.944
<i>Doesn't mean we don't miss you.</i>

00:34.969 --> 00:37.649
You keep saying that you need
to know who you are without cancer.

00:37.674 --> 00:40.020
Maybe I need to figure out
who I am without <i>you.</i>

00:40.044 --> 00:41.929
<i>I just wish I could've
been there for you...</i>

00:41.954 --> 00:44.067
I didn't stay by your side
and Rutledge you through chemo

00:44.091 --> 00:45.823
so you could piss your life away.

00:45.848 --> 00:47.153
<i>... the way you were for us.</i>

00:47.178 --> 00:48.611
You're gonna beat this.

00:51.109 --> 00:54.695
[MONITORS BEEPING, GAS HISSING]

00:54.720 --> 00:56.301
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ON VIDEO GAME]

00:56.326 --> 00:58.871
GARY: Jon, after this game,
why don't you take it easy, okay?

00:58.896 --> 01:00.023
Here comes Kyrie.

01:00.048 --> 01:01.292
And from <i>way</i> downtown...

01:01.317 --> 01:03.529
Bang! And the crowd goes wild!

01:03.554 --> 01:05.835
Whoa, dude. Your IV.

01:05.860 --> 01:07.414
Oh, and he steals the ball!

01:07.439 --> 01:09.078
Would you stop moving, please?

01:09.103 --> 01:10.609
Hey, you're running out of time.

01:10.634 --> 01:12.390
- [WHISTLE BLOWS]
- What?

01:12.415 --> 01:14.375
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE CONTINUE]

01:14.400 --> 01:17.109
Well, if I can get this back in,
<i>you'll</i> have more time, alright?

01:17.134 --> 01:18.476
- MAN: <i>Oh!</i>
- [WHISTLE BLOWS]

01:18.501 --> 01:20.146
- What is this?
- Tatum sets the moving pick.

01:20.170 --> 01:21.314
Why is this not...

01:21.339 --> 01:23.421
♪♪

01:23.446 --> 01:24.823
Phone charger?

01:24.848 --> 01:26.148
Jon, this isn't...

01:26.429 --> 01:28.390
Mendez moves the ball down court...

01:28.415 --> 01:29.696
Oh, but he gets trapped in the corner!

01:29.720 --> 01:31.672
- This isn't gonna work, man.
- What's he gonna do?

01:31.696 --> 01:34.164
There's 10 seconds left.
Can he get the shot?

01:34.189 --> 01:36.367
I need some help in here!
Somebody help me!

01:36.392 --> 01:37.392
Eight...

01:37.417 --> 01:39.195
CROWD: <i>Seven, six,</i>

01:39.220 --> 01:41.117
- <i>five, four, three...</i>
- [BUZZER]

01:41.142 --> 01:44.007
- Is this really what you want?
- <i>... two, one.</i>

01:44.032 --> 01:45.390
[BUZZER BLARES, ECHOES]

01:45.415 --> 01:46.640
Too late, Gary.

01:46.665 --> 01:48.656
- No. No.
- It's over.

01:48.681 --> 01:49.890
Maggie, wait!

01:49.915 --> 01:51.481
I... [SIGHS]

01:53.041 --> 01:54.679
Jon. Jon?!

01:54.704 --> 01:56.859
[INHALES SHARPLY]

01:56.884 --> 01:59.406
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

02:00.398 --> 02:05.257
Synced & corrected by QueenMaddie
www.addic7ed.com

02:05.449 --> 02:07.359
<i>Hey, it's Jon.</i>

02:07.384 --> 02:09.532
<i>I was hoping to speak to you,
not just leave a message,</i>

02:09.556 --> 02:11.367
<i>but, uh...</i>

02:11.392 --> 02:13.539
<i>I just need you to do me a favor.</i>

02:14.797 --> 02:16.575
<i>Love each other.</i>

02:16.600 --> 02:18.265
[CHARLIE COOS]

02:18.290 --> 02:20.156
Is that the voicemail again?

02:20.181 --> 02:21.181
[SIGHS]

02:21.206 --> 02:23.835
Eddie, you have
to stop torturing yourself.

02:23.860 --> 02:25.664
[SIGHS] I don't think I should go

02:25.689 --> 02:28.135
to this dinner for Jon tonight.

02:28.160 --> 02:30.398
Of course you should! It's been a year.

02:30.423 --> 02:31.648
Delilah wants everyone there.

02:31.673 --> 02:33.796
Well, Sophie doesn't.

02:33.973 --> 02:36.018
She's barely talked to me in months.

02:36.043 --> 02:37.812
[SIGHS] She just...

02:38.253 --> 02:40.117
needs more time.

02:41.064 --> 02:42.601
Yeah, I guess.

02:42.626 --> 02:44.037
Hey, you look great.

02:44.062 --> 02:45.867
- Oh, yeah?
- You ready for your interview?

02:45.892 --> 02:47.391
I thought you were gonna
wear the pinstripes.

02:47.415 --> 02:50.398
I was. But Charlie thought
this would be better.

02:50.423 --> 02:52.320
Oh, yeah? How'd she tell you that?

02:52.345 --> 02:54.250
- She spit up all over the other one.
- Ah.

02:54.275 --> 02:56.889
But that's okay, Charlie,
'cause you were totally right.

02:56.914 --> 03:00.882
All hail Pharaoh Theo!

03:00.907 --> 03:01.907
What is happening?

03:01.932 --> 03:03.576
It's for his biography presentation.

03:03.601 --> 03:05.579
He picked King Tut.

03:05.604 --> 03:08.562
He was only 9 years old when he ruled.

03:08.587 --> 03:10.859
Back then, the laws were a lot looser.

03:10.884 --> 03:11.960
[CHUCKLES]

03:11.985 --> 03:13.976
I was clearly born at the wrong time.

03:14.001 --> 03:15.367
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

03:15.392 --> 03:16.571
Oh, that must be Darcy and Liam.

03:16.595 --> 03:19.531
Liam, the purpose of the knock
is for them to let <i>you</i> in.

03:19.556 --> 03:20.557
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- We're here!

03:20.581 --> 03:22.367
- Liam, shoes.
- Hey, Darcy.

03:22.392 --> 03:24.531
- Liam's here!
- Oh, hey. Cool hat.

03:24.556 --> 03:26.563
- LIAM: Hey, Theo.
- Thanks again for watching the kids.

03:26.587 --> 03:27.766
- Sure. No problem.
- I got to run.

03:27.790 --> 03:28.889
Hey.

03:29.406 --> 03:31.164
You got this. Crush it.

03:31.189 --> 03:32.484
Totally crush it.

03:32.509 --> 03:34.375
Consider it crushed.

03:35.609 --> 03:37.734
GARY: Okay, this is
gonna be a little awkward...

03:38.505 --> 03:40.968
but it's better that you're
hearing this from a friend...

03:40.993 --> 03:42.125
You're white.

03:42.150 --> 03:43.609
You cannot pull off those shoes.

03:43.634 --> 03:44.766
Don't worry about the parking.

03:44.790 --> 03:46.869
Dad, I'm picking you up
and taking you there.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.072
Dude, hurry up and get off the phone.

03:48.096 --> 03:49.297
We're making fun of Ed's shoes.

03:49.321 --> 03:51.359
Pops, we talked about this.

03:51.384 --> 03:52.428
You are going.

03:52.453 --> 03:54.132
I-I'm picking you up at noon.

03:54.157 --> 03:55.234
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

03:55.259 --> 03:56.789
- Your dad, huh?
- Yeah.

03:56.814 --> 03:58.657
I'm taking him to his first
therapy session later.

03:58.681 --> 04:00.640
That shrink is gonna need a shrink.

04:00.955 --> 04:03.710
Gentlemen,
I am glad we are doing this today.

04:03.735 --> 04:05.012
- Yeah, man.
- Yeah, me too.

04:05.037 --> 04:07.187
And if Jon were here,
I know exactly what he'd do.

04:07.212 --> 04:09.695
He would huddle us in a circle,
and he'd say,

04:09.720 --> 04:11.953
"What in the hell are those?"

04:12.289 --> 04:13.498
I told you.

04:13.523 --> 04:14.898
What? They're cool!

04:14.923 --> 04:16.812
Yeah, like, on Nick Cannon.

04:16.837 --> 04:18.546
[CHUCKLES]

04:18.571 --> 04:20.115
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

04:20.279 --> 04:22.796
Mr. Mendez. Texting, or you playing?

04:22.821 --> 04:24.835
Oh, he's playing. Just a different game.

04:24.860 --> 04:26.781
Last night, he went one-on-one

04:26.806 --> 04:28.812
with the cashier from
that new laser tag place,

04:28.837 --> 04:30.218
which we can now never go to.

04:30.243 --> 04:31.546
Wait, you got her number

04:31.571 --> 04:33.703
while you were
chaperoning Theo's playdate?

04:33.728 --> 04:36.196
- Look, I...
- May I field this one?

04:36.220 --> 04:38.754
Theo's friend's mom scored the digits.

04:38.920 --> 04:41.070
You got a mom to do your dirty work?

04:41.095 --> 04:42.945
- I know.
- It's whack, right?

04:43.320 --> 04:44.679
"Digits"?

04:44.704 --> 04:45.915
"Whack"?

04:45.940 --> 04:47.884
This is why you can't wear those shoes.

04:47.909 --> 04:49.625
- [CHUCKLES]
- You know what?

04:49.956 --> 04:51.257
[CHUCKLES]

04:51.413 --> 04:52.936
Am I doing this right?

04:53.417 --> 04:55.251
Honestly?

04:55.276 --> 04:56.654
Sure.

04:56.744 --> 04:58.195
Just crank evenly.

04:58.220 --> 04:59.351
Okay.

04:59.376 --> 05:00.460
Evenly.

05:00.485 --> 05:01.859
[WHISPERING] I thought I was.

05:01.884 --> 05:03.132
[CHUCKLES]

05:04.130 --> 05:05.757
Hi!

05:05.782 --> 05:07.039
- Hi.
- Hi!

05:07.064 --> 05:08.908
I just dropped by
to see if I could help.

05:08.933 --> 05:10.144
Perfect timing.

05:10.169 --> 05:11.554
She's tagging in.

05:11.579 --> 05:13.140
- Mwah.
- You know what? This is good.

05:13.165 --> 05:15.460
I actually need to take
care of some stuff at work.

05:15.485 --> 05:16.835
But I will be back tonight.

05:16.860 --> 05:18.296
Thank you.

05:18.321 --> 05:20.835
And thank you all for being here.

05:20.860 --> 05:22.704
It means a lot to me and the kids.

05:22.729 --> 05:25.406
Even though he's gone,
Jon's still bringing us together.

05:27.835 --> 05:30.718
I'm sorry, D. Uh, I didn't mean to...

05:30.743 --> 05:32.492
What? No. No, no, no, no. It's not you.

05:32.517 --> 05:35.523
No. It's just, um... Just the whole day.

05:36.037 --> 05:38.851
I'm gonna go, uh, get some dishes.

05:38.876 --> 05:40.734
- D?
- Yeah, let me.

05:41.204 --> 05:45.233
You just, uh, stay here
and crank evenly.

05:45.258 --> 05:47.194
Mm-hmm. That's right.

05:48.283 --> 05:49.811
How'd the job interview go?

05:49.836 --> 05:52.257
They made me an offer in the room.

05:52.282 --> 05:54.124
Well, don't sound so excited.

05:54.149 --> 05:55.828
There's something that
one of the partners said

05:55.852 --> 05:58.077
that bugged me.

05:58.102 --> 06:00.733
He said, "You know, it'll be good

06:00.758 --> 06:02.663
to have someone like <i>you on the team."</i>

06:02.688 --> 06:05.172
Oh, God, and let me guess.
He had no idea how offensive that was.

06:05.196 --> 06:06.707
None.

06:06.732 --> 06:10.249
I just feel like I'm going
out of the frying pan

06:10.274 --> 06:13.233
into another frying pan.

06:13.274 --> 06:15.070
Well, if you don't think
it's gonna make you happy,

06:15.094 --> 06:16.889
hold out for something else.

06:17.393 --> 06:19.171
I'm sorry.

06:19.196 --> 06:21.452
Today's not the day to talk about this.

06:21.477 --> 06:22.988
Hey.

06:23.013 --> 06:25.757
A year ago, our friend killed himself.

06:25.782 --> 06:28.968
I can't think of a better time
to talk about our happiness.

06:32.838 --> 06:34.678
How are the kids doing?

06:35.000 --> 06:37.968
Sometimes I feel
they're stronger than I am.

06:37.993 --> 06:39.937
Oh, and if today wasn't hard enough,

06:39.962 --> 06:43.077
guess who texted while
we were at the cemetery?

06:43.944 --> 06:45.428
- Miles.
- Okay.

06:45.453 --> 06:47.632
Yeah, admittedly, not the best timing.

06:47.657 --> 06:49.335
- You think?
- [LAUGHS]

06:49.360 --> 06:50.609
It was supposed to be a one-night thing.

06:50.633 --> 06:51.968
I don't know why he's texting.

06:51.993 --> 06:55.241
Oh, that's because Millennials
prefer texting over phone calls.

06:55.266 --> 06:58.038
Exactly. He's way too young for me.

06:58.063 --> 07:00.358
Our lives are completely different.

07:00.383 --> 07:03.444
Yeah, 'cause his life is
texting a beautiful woman,

07:03.469 --> 07:06.491
and your life is ignoring a hot man.

07:06.516 --> 07:08.772
Whatever happened
to having a little fun?

07:09.414 --> 07:11.692
I'm not sure I'm ready to move on.

07:11.717 --> 07:13.749
Well, if you're not ready, that's fine.

07:13.774 --> 07:16.077
But if it's because
you feel guilty or...

07:16.102 --> 07:18.499
you think you don't deserve it,

07:18.524 --> 07:20.241
I don't accept that.

07:21.079 --> 07:22.655
[CHUCKLES]

07:22.680 --> 07:24.163
That's... That's got to be the worst

07:24.188 --> 07:25.422
I think I've ever seen you play.

07:25.446 --> 07:27.624
- He's gonna think...
- It's the shoes!

07:27.851 --> 07:30.022
- You see what you did?
- Sorry.

07:31.866 --> 07:33.772
Hey, uh...

07:33.797 --> 07:36.743
I had that dream about
him again last night.

07:36.768 --> 07:38.100
[ZIPPER CLOSES]

07:38.125 --> 07:40.968
There were some fun
new additions this time.

07:41.089 --> 07:42.897
Maggie was there. [CHUCKLES]

07:42.922 --> 07:45.132
Leaving me again. It was awesome.

07:45.157 --> 07:48.553
And the chemo machine was
plugged in with a-a phone charger.

07:48.578 --> 07:50.139
[LAUGHS]

07:50.164 --> 07:52.819
Come on! No jokes about me dumping women

07:52.844 --> 07:54.622
for leaving phone chargers at my place?

07:54.647 --> 07:57.772
If you recall, Jon was all
over that last time we saw him.

07:58.323 --> 08:00.335
A year ago, I called you out

08:00.360 --> 08:02.061
for not quitting a job that you hated

08:02.086 --> 08:04.710
and you for staying
in a loveless marriage.

08:05.093 --> 08:06.593
Congratulations. You both did it.

08:06.618 --> 08:08.312
You... you...
you both turned your life around.

08:08.336 --> 08:09.714
Me?

08:09.739 --> 08:11.514
Nothing's changed.

08:12.101 --> 08:13.679
Still pissing my life away.

08:13.704 --> 08:15.202
Gary, don't say that. Come on.

08:15.227 --> 08:18.280
I am incapable... of real emotion.

08:18.305 --> 08:22.061
Although, to be fair,
emotion can be dangerous.

08:22.086 --> 08:23.496
Just ask the guy who offed himself.

08:23.521 --> 08:24.966
Oh, wait, we can't.

08:24.991 --> 08:26.210
- Whoa.
- Dude. [SCOFFS]

08:26.235 --> 08:27.501
Careful what you say. Last person who

08:27.525 --> 08:29.828
questioned my life decisions
ended up killing themself.

08:29.853 --> 08:31.765
So bust my balls,

08:31.790 --> 08:33.821
then find a tall building
to throw yourselves off of.

08:33.845 --> 08:35.722
[CHUCKLES]

08:35.748 --> 08:38.780
♪♪

08:40.188 --> 08:41.999
EDDIE: There's my angry friend.

08:42.023 --> 08:43.155
[SIGHS]

08:43.179 --> 08:44.268
Where's Rome?

08:44.293 --> 08:45.416
[BAG THUDS]

08:45.441 --> 08:47.860
He's driving his dad to therapy.

08:48.395 --> 08:50.608
GARY: He should've taken me with him.

08:50.632 --> 08:52.155
Sorry about all that. [SIGHS]

08:52.180 --> 08:53.277
Believe me.

08:53.301 --> 08:55.633
[PATS BACK] I get it.

08:56.171 --> 08:58.546
I dreamt about him last week.

09:00.950 --> 09:02.593
That guy gets around.

09:02.618 --> 09:03.913
[CHUCKLES]

09:03.938 --> 09:08.040
Yeah, I don't remember much,
but it was weird.

09:08.809 --> 09:11.819
We were on a boat, and I was drinking...

09:11.844 --> 09:13.389
[BELL DINGS IN DISTANCE]

09:13.414 --> 09:15.913
Mm. [LAUGHS]

09:15.938 --> 09:17.522
Hey, grab me another beer, will you?

09:17.547 --> 09:19.304
You know I can't do that.

09:19.681 --> 09:20.792
Fine.

09:20.817 --> 09:22.762
I'll just get it myself.

09:27.252 --> 09:28.696
[GRUNTS]

09:28.721 --> 09:31.901
[WATER SPLASHING]

09:32.507 --> 09:33.819
Jon?

09:33.844 --> 09:35.377
Jon!

09:35.965 --> 09:37.330
Jon!

09:38.414 --> 09:40.080
[MUFFLED] Jon!

09:41.542 --> 09:43.815
Aah! Jon!

09:43.840 --> 09:45.096
Just grab my hand!

09:45.121 --> 09:46.815
Right... Grab my hand!

09:54.559 --> 09:57.420
When I finally got ahold of him,
it wasn't him.

09:58.135 --> 10:01.443
It was this girl's hand
reaching out to me.

10:01.468 --> 10:03.561
All I remember

10:03.586 --> 10:06.193
is this teal nail polish.

10:07.873 --> 10:09.904
Weird, huh?

10:10.356 --> 10:12.389
Is it?

10:12.750 --> 10:14.995
You know, I don't think you need Freud

10:15.020 --> 10:16.765
to figure this one out.

10:16.790 --> 10:18.740
Who else you feeling guilty about?

10:20.028 --> 10:22.037
- A teenage girl maybe?
- [SIGHS]

10:22.565 --> 10:24.959
Sophie. Of course.

10:25.367 --> 10:27.732
And the beer is because
you're an alcoholic.

10:28.222 --> 10:29.222
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

10:29.247 --> 10:30.646
Thanks.

10:31.071 --> 10:34.053
Your mom, she loved her hymns.

10:34.078 --> 10:35.131
Yeah, I know, Pop.

10:35.156 --> 10:37.046
But we're gonna miss your
appointment if we don't leave soon.

10:37.070 --> 10:39.397
Good, 'cause I don't even know
what I'm supposed to talk about.

10:39.421 --> 10:41.248
He's just gonna ask you some questions,

10:41.280 --> 10:42.786
and you're gonna have a conversation.

10:42.811 --> 10:45.389
And you'll see...
having somebody to talk to is great.

10:45.414 --> 10:47.021
Why can't I talk to Maggie?

10:47.046 --> 10:48.457
At least she's not a stranger.

10:48.482 --> 10:50.623
Not appropriate. Believe me, I've tried.

10:50.648 --> 10:52.256
I like her.

10:52.365 --> 10:53.865
She fought cancer.

10:53.890 --> 10:55.021
That takes guts.

10:55.046 --> 10:57.373
Totally. Let's talk about it in the car.

10:58.146 --> 10:59.842
I read your script.

11:02.904 --> 11:03.982
[SCRIPT THUDS]

11:04.007 --> 11:05.210
Found it in your mother's drawer

11:05.234 --> 11:06.712
when I was going through her things.

11:06.737 --> 11:10.904
The cover says, "Based on a true story."

11:11.427 --> 11:12.967
So, is it true?

11:12.992 --> 11:15.357
The part about you
taking all those pills?

11:18.168 --> 11:19.475
Yeah.

11:20.728 --> 11:23.459
- But I'm in a much better place...
- How could you not tell me?

11:25.815 --> 11:26.926
I tried to tell you.

11:26.951 --> 11:28.429
Was that before or after

11:28.454 --> 11:30.295
you decided to write a
whole movie about it?

11:30.320 --> 11:32.217
What do you think I was trying to do

11:32.242 --> 11:33.519
the day that we fixed my sink?

11:33.544 --> 11:34.600
And all you ended up doing

11:34.625 --> 11:36.764
was shaming me for
taking antidepressants.

11:36.789 --> 11:38.900
When we lost your mother,

11:38.925 --> 11:41.871
you said we needed to talk more.

11:41.896 --> 11:44.365
The whole reason I
agreed to see a shrink

11:44.390 --> 11:47.240
was because <i>we</i> were
trying to do things differently.

11:47.265 --> 11:48.826
So you know what?

11:49.184 --> 11:51.154
I'm not going.

11:51.405 --> 11:52.749
Why should I talk to anyone

11:52.774 --> 11:55.108
when you can't even
talk to your own father?

11:57.848 --> 11:59.701
See?

12:00.396 --> 12:01.951
This.

12:02.680 --> 12:06.889
Your reaction is exactly
why I didn't tell you.

12:07.379 --> 12:10.990
You find out that I...
I tried to kill myself,

12:11.015 --> 12:13.396
and instead of making
sure that I'm okay,

12:13.421 --> 12:15.193
once again, you attack me.

12:15.218 --> 12:18.092
Talking about Maggie's
brave for fighting cancer?

12:18.117 --> 12:20.862
I'm... I'm fighting a disease!

12:20.887 --> 12:22.693
I'm brave, too!

12:23.298 --> 12:24.607
You know what?

12:24.632 --> 12:26.777
Do what you want. Do what you want.

12:26.802 --> 12:29.209
I don't care if you don't go.

12:29.234 --> 12:30.967
I'm done trying to help you.

12:33.409 --> 12:35.677
[DOORBELL RINGS]

12:41.226 --> 12:43.193
[SIGHS] Mom, Eddie's here.

12:43.218 --> 12:45.928
Uh, hey, ac... actually,
can we talk for a second?

12:45.953 --> 12:47.521
[DOOR CLOSES]

12:48.148 --> 12:49.678
[BAG THUDS]

12:51.631 --> 12:53.966
I heard you haven't been playing guitar.

12:55.417 --> 12:57.271
[SIGHS]

12:57.296 --> 12:59.459
♪♪

12:59.484 --> 13:03.389
Look, all I know is that...

13:04.397 --> 13:06.864
during the toughest times of my life,

13:06.889 --> 13:08.818
music was there for me.

13:08.843 --> 13:13.311
And I just don't want you to
give up something that you love

13:14.060 --> 13:17.615
and something that you are so good at.

13:19.322 --> 13:20.833
[SIGHS]

13:21.318 --> 13:23.279
Well, you're right, Eddie.

13:23.819 --> 13:25.779
Music is an escape.

13:26.460 --> 13:28.771
Or at least it should be.

13:28.796 --> 13:30.874
Except now,
every time I pick up a guitar,

13:30.899 --> 13:32.777
all I think about is you.

13:32.931 --> 13:36.162
It was bad enough
what you did to my dad,

13:36.187 --> 13:39.389
but during all those lessons,
during all those songs,

13:39.956 --> 13:42.139
you were also lying to me.

13:44.093 --> 13:45.605
[SIGHS] Soph...

13:45.630 --> 13:47.074
Don't.

13:47.099 --> 13:49.066
[SIGHS]

13:50.658 --> 13:51.803
I'm sorry.

13:51.828 --> 13:52.959
No, it's okay.

13:52.984 --> 13:54.076
I'll talk to her.

13:54.101 --> 13:55.584
She's upset. We...

13:55.609 --> 13:58.162
We went to the cemetery this morning.

13:58.187 --> 13:59.420
[SIGHS]

14:00.421 --> 14:02.654
You still haven't been, have you?

14:02.679 --> 14:04.443
You should go, Eddie. It's time.

14:04.468 --> 14:06.725
- You haven't been since the funeral.
- I know.

14:08.493 --> 14:10.038
It's just...

14:10.140 --> 14:13.568
How can I ask for forgiveness from Jon

14:13.593 --> 14:15.857
when his own daughter
won't even forgive me?

14:24.762 --> 14:26.551
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

14:32.681 --> 14:34.292
Smoothies.

14:34.317 --> 14:35.528
Uh-oh.

14:35.553 --> 14:37.988
To what do I owe the pleasure?

14:38.013 --> 14:39.624
I saw my dad,

14:39.649 --> 14:41.660
and I bought you a smoothie,

14:41.685 --> 14:44.496
and I thought I'd talk to
you while you drank it.

14:47.641 --> 14:50.021
Got you the largest one they had.

14:50.434 --> 14:51.918
Great.

14:51.943 --> 14:53.655
Well, if you don't want the job,
don't take it.

14:53.679 --> 14:55.246
What am I supposed to do? Not work?

14:55.271 --> 14:57.770
You've always talked about
hanging your own shingle.

14:58.029 --> 15:00.715
- Why not now?
- [LAUGHS] Are you kidding?

15:00.740 --> 15:03.285
We can't afford that.
The startup costs are huge.

15:03.310 --> 15:04.621
We have savings.

15:04.646 --> 15:06.293
And plus, the label's already talking

15:06.318 --> 15:07.849
about pairing me with some new artists.

15:07.873 --> 15:09.543
Eddie, I can't put it all on you.

15:09.568 --> 15:11.279
Yes, you can.

15:11.304 --> 15:16.066
Katherine, after all the years
of supporting my dreams,

15:16.091 --> 15:18.809
let me finally support yours.

15:19.632 --> 15:21.949
For the first time in a very long time,

15:21.974 --> 15:24.535
I've got this. I have got us.

15:27.092 --> 15:28.832
ROME: I couldn't believe it.

15:29.244 --> 15:32.746
Well, the truth is,
your dad probably feels guilty.

15:32.771 --> 15:37.107
But that does not
make his response okay.

15:39.420 --> 15:42.957
You came into my life at
just the right moment.

15:42.982 --> 15:44.560
Seriously, I-I do not know

15:44.585 --> 15:46.730
what I would do without you.

15:46.755 --> 15:51.236
♪♪

15:51.261 --> 15:52.868
- Whoa.
- [CRYING]

15:52.893 --> 15:54.431
Maggie, are you alright?

15:55.208 --> 15:56.517
Oh, God, Maggie, you're not...?

15:56.542 --> 15:58.087
No, no, I'm o... I'm fine.

15:58.112 --> 16:01.134
[SNIFFLES] I'm healthy. I just...

16:01.666 --> 16:05.454
[SIGHS] What is the, uh...
The rule here

16:05.479 --> 16:09.079
when it's patient-doctor
confidentiality?

16:09.321 --> 16:11.407
For us patients?

16:11.653 --> 16:13.040
Strictly enforced. Why?

16:13.065 --> 16:15.454
I haven't told anyone this yet, but...

16:16.752 --> 16:18.486
I got the Oxford Fellowship.

16:18.511 --> 16:20.978
[LAUGHS] Maggie, that's fantastic!

16:21.003 --> 16:22.954
[CHUCKLES]

16:22.979 --> 16:24.456
Isn't it?

16:24.711 --> 16:26.422
Why am I more excited than you are?

16:26.447 --> 16:28.259
Oh, I'm excited.

16:28.284 --> 16:29.946
It's everything I wanted. I just...

16:29.971 --> 16:33.634
For the first time in my life, I'm...

16:34.200 --> 16:36.681
I'm not sure I want to leave.

16:38.292 --> 16:39.533
DELILAH: You're gonna set the timer?

16:39.557 --> 16:41.165
Woman, this is not my first rodeo.

16:41.190 --> 16:42.190
- Oh, hey!
- GARY: Hey.

16:42.215 --> 16:44.689
Thanks for being here. Ohh.

16:44.714 --> 16:47.462
Is that Eddie's, uh,
soccer mom van I saw driving away?

16:47.487 --> 16:49.704
Yeah, he took Katherine
home so she could change.

16:49.729 --> 16:52.907
But hopefully he's coming back, too.

16:53.558 --> 16:55.237
I know I'm early.

16:55.785 --> 16:58.314
Have a beer. [CHUCKLES]

16:58.339 --> 17:00.502
[EXHALES SHARPLY] I slept with
this girl I met at laser tag.

17:00.526 --> 17:02.892
And you came early to tell us that?

17:02.917 --> 17:04.867
Yeah, actually.

17:05.342 --> 17:07.134
I mean, I knew I needed to end it.

17:07.159 --> 17:08.923
Probably shouldn't have started it.

17:09.132 --> 17:13.742
But instead of ghosting
her or texting her...

17:13.768 --> 17:16.892
Which I've heard some other men do...

17:17.218 --> 17:19.367
I showed up like a gentleman...

17:19.730 --> 17:21.762
- Nice...
- ... and did it properly. Yeah.

17:22.214 --> 17:25.798
Okay, well, I'm sure
she really appreciated that.

17:25.823 --> 17:27.320
She did. I mean, she's totally fine.

17:27.346 --> 17:28.853
- [BOTTLE THUDS]
- It's me.

17:30.017 --> 17:32.009
I don't know what to do now.

17:32.034 --> 17:33.337
- Um...
- Um...

17:33.362 --> 17:34.946
You can help with the salad.

17:34.971 --> 17:36.868
No, I mean my life.

17:37.485 --> 17:40.298
[SIGHS] I don't know how
I'm gonna fix my life.

17:40.323 --> 17:42.806
So, what prompted
this existential crisis?

17:42.831 --> 17:44.329
Your husband.

17:44.354 --> 17:46.654
He's haunting my dreams now.

17:47.597 --> 17:49.231
Oh.

17:50.246 --> 17:52.458
I wish I had dreams about him.

17:52.483 --> 17:54.720
I never do anymore. [CHUCKLES]

17:54.745 --> 17:57.454
It's almost like he
doesn't want to talk to me.

17:58.088 --> 17:59.131
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

17:59.156 --> 18:01.439
Oh, uh, pardon me.

18:01.464 --> 18:03.965
Hey, babe. Yeah, how'd it go?

18:05.006 --> 18:06.509
Wait, what do you mean?

18:06.534 --> 18:07.915
What's going on?

18:08.260 --> 18:09.540
REGINA: Walter!

18:10.283 --> 18:11.368
Walter.

18:11.393 --> 18:13.314
♪ <i>... God</i> ♪

18:13.339 --> 18:15.735
Did you not hear me ring the bell?

18:16.070 --> 18:21.306
♪ <i>The children of God</i> ♪

18:22.018 --> 18:23.463
[MUSIC STOPS]

18:23.656 --> 18:25.034
If you're here because of what happened,

18:25.058 --> 18:26.591
it wasn't my fault.

18:27.368 --> 18:29.915
He didn't tell me either.

18:31.276 --> 18:32.934
- What?
- I found his suicide note

18:32.959 --> 18:34.376
in a drawer weeks later.

18:34.401 --> 18:35.907
So I get it.

18:35.932 --> 18:37.843
I was upset, too.

18:37.868 --> 18:40.907
But then I got over it
because he needed me.

18:41.527 --> 18:43.220
He needs you, too.

18:43.245 --> 18:44.489
For what?

18:44.514 --> 18:46.837
To be there for him.

18:46.862 --> 18:50.860
♪♪

18:50.885 --> 18:52.571
I know you love him,

18:53.421 --> 18:57.087
but you make it so
hard for him to see that.

18:57.112 --> 18:59.385
- That's not true.
- Oh, Walter, come on!

18:59.410 --> 19:01.158
It took him 30 years to find out

19:01.183 --> 19:03.529
that you were the one who put
those stars above his bunk bed

19:03.553 --> 19:05.152
when he was a kid.

19:06.324 --> 19:08.869
The dinner we're going to tonight?

19:09.425 --> 19:12.385
It could've just as
easily been for Rome.

19:12.410 --> 19:14.510
Walter, I almost lost my husband.

19:14.535 --> 19:16.463
You almost lost your son.

19:17.627 --> 19:19.065
You know what I think?

19:19.090 --> 19:20.894
I think you're scared to
look too closely at him

19:20.918 --> 19:23.604
because you might end up
seeing yourself there.

19:30.063 --> 19:33.965
[SILVERWARE CLACKING SOFTLY]

19:33.990 --> 19:36.470
[INHALES SHARPLY]

19:36.495 --> 19:38.973
[CLEARS THROAT, SIGHS]

19:39.264 --> 19:40.925
I, uh...

19:42.273 --> 19:45.824
I heard about you and Eddie.

19:46.503 --> 19:47.871
[SIGHS]

19:47.896 --> 19:49.144
Yeah, look, I...

19:49.169 --> 19:50.847
I don't really want to talk about it.

19:50.872 --> 19:52.332
Great.

19:53.460 --> 19:54.730
I'll talk, then.

19:54.755 --> 19:56.333
[SILVERWARE CLATTERS]

19:56.358 --> 19:58.136
[SIGHS]

19:58.161 --> 20:00.906
♪♪

20:00.931 --> 20:02.777
I'm mad, too.

20:04.847 --> 20:06.681
What he did was terrible.

20:08.214 --> 20:11.144
But if I let that one thing

20:11.169 --> 20:13.558
undermine everything else...

20:14.923 --> 20:16.668
then when he said
that he cared about me,

20:16.693 --> 20:18.238
I don't believe it.

20:19.732 --> 20:21.551
When he said he was my friend,
I don't believe him.

20:21.575 --> 20:25.210
When he said that, uh,
he was looking out for me...

20:26.324 --> 20:28.192
... I don't believe it.

20:31.170 --> 20:36.419
And yet, somehow, I found a
way to forgive your dad.

20:40.726 --> 20:43.670
You see, Soph, I need to
believe that he loved me, okay?

20:43.695 --> 20:45.205
I need to believe that.

20:45.230 --> 20:49.311
So I will not let that
one thing that he did

20:49.336 --> 20:52.983
undermine all the other things
that he did <i>for</i> me.

20:55.640 --> 20:58.275
You can't let one
mistake define a person.

21:00.735 --> 21:02.506
[DOORBELL RINGS]

21:03.055 --> 21:04.202
[DOOR OPENS]

21:04.227 --> 21:05.858
- Hey, guys. Come on in.
- Hi.

21:05.883 --> 21:07.894
- Hey, Danny.
- Hi.

21:08.285 --> 21:09.285
Cool hat.

21:09.310 --> 21:11.155
Technically it's a headdress.

21:11.180 --> 21:12.891
Yeah, it is!

21:12.916 --> 21:14.851
You know, you get weirder
every time I see you, kid.

21:14.875 --> 21:16.031
[CHUCKLING] Thanks, Uncle Gary.

21:16.055 --> 21:17.991
- You got it.
- Come on.

21:18.016 --> 21:20.733
So, tell me about this headdress.

21:20.758 --> 21:23.264
- Oh, it's a presentation at school.
- Wow.

21:23.289 --> 21:25.444
- DELILAH: Is that Jon's scotch set?
- Hey.

21:25.469 --> 21:26.980
Aww.

21:27.323 --> 21:30.850
After dinner, I thought
we could toast Jon together.

21:30.875 --> 21:32.053
Seems only fitting.

21:32.078 --> 21:34.044
- I'd love that.
- Okay.

21:37.545 --> 21:39.023
[DOOR CLOSES]

21:39.048 --> 21:40.913
- Hey.
- Hey.

21:40.938 --> 21:42.608
GARY: [ENGLISH ACCENT] Well!

21:42.633 --> 21:45.647
If it isn't Baroness Bloom.

21:45.672 --> 21:47.897
Brought us some crisps, have you?

21:48.666 --> 21:50.277
Why are you doing an English accent?

21:50.302 --> 21:52.850
[NORMAL ACCENT] Oh,
we've been playing "Downton Abbey."

21:52.875 --> 21:54.405
Danny's a big fan.

21:55.873 --> 21:57.889
Oh. [SIGHS]

21:57.914 --> 22:00.139
When are those two
getting back together?

22:00.481 --> 22:02.425
No time soon.

22:02.450 --> 22:03.761
Why would you say that?

22:03.786 --> 22:05.330
Um, what? I don't... I don't know.

22:05.355 --> 22:06.667
Why... Why would you say your thing?

22:06.691 --> 22:08.686
[GASPS] Rome. What do you know?

22:08.971 --> 22:10.782
Things. What do <i>you</i> know?

22:13.673 --> 22:15.174
[GLASSES CLINKING]

22:16.161 --> 22:17.657
- Ladies.
- Mm.

22:19.615 --> 22:20.923
Oh, look at you!

22:20.948 --> 22:23.774
Bringing cheese dip,
even though you're lactose intol.

22:23.799 --> 22:25.102
Now, that's a friend.

22:25.127 --> 22:26.471
[CHUCKLES]

22:26.496 --> 22:27.963
- MAGGIE: Hey.
- So, he bought her a bottle of wine

22:27.987 --> 22:29.861
so that she wouldn't feel
bad about being stood up?

22:29.885 --> 22:32.321
- What's in the bag?
- Yeah, and she had no idea.

22:32.346 --> 22:34.977
And I promised I wouldn't tell... her.

22:35.002 --> 22:38.181
Which was fine, until she
told me she wished it was Gary.

22:38.535 --> 22:39.696
What does that mean?

22:39.721 --> 22:41.465
It means she's still in love with him,

22:41.490 --> 22:44.415
he's still in love with her,
and neither will admit it.

22:45.141 --> 22:46.727
What are you two whispering about?

22:46.752 --> 22:48.872
- Nothing. And lasagna.
- Lasagna.

22:49.481 --> 22:51.051
- What's up?
- You know when you said

22:51.076 --> 22:53.278
you wished there was
something we could do

22:53.303 --> 22:55.520
- to help honor Jon?
- Yeah.

22:55.545 --> 22:57.590
I think I have an idea.

22:57.794 --> 23:00.031
- [KNOCK ON DOOR]
- Coming!

23:06.188 --> 23:07.711
Sophie.

23:08.583 --> 23:09.760
What are you doing here?

23:09.785 --> 23:11.398
I need you to come with me.

23:17.318 --> 23:19.983
[GEARSHIFT CLICKS, ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

23:26.552 --> 23:29.335
I heard my mom say that
you hadn't visited yet.

23:29.360 --> 23:33.077
Look, I'm just so tired of being mad.

23:33.873 --> 23:36.118
I just want to move on.

23:40.089 --> 23:41.940
You should visit him.

23:45.135 --> 23:47.914
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

24:04.564 --> 24:05.564
[WATER RUNNING]

24:05.830 --> 24:07.510
- Oh, God! Sorry, sorry.
- Whoa!

24:07.535 --> 24:08.879
[CHUCKLES] It's okay.

24:08.904 --> 24:10.214
- [WATER SHUTS OFF]
- [INHALES SHARPLY]

24:10.238 --> 24:13.057
But, hey, it's not the first time
we've met up in a bathroom.

24:13.082 --> 24:14.744
Yeah.

24:14.769 --> 24:16.291
Right back where we started.

24:16.316 --> 24:18.197
Been feeling that all day.

24:18.222 --> 24:19.766
Mm.

24:19.791 --> 24:21.713
[SIGHS]

24:24.455 --> 24:26.523
Hey, uh...

24:30.138 --> 24:34.436
When I first met you,
[SIGHS] you were dying.

24:34.772 --> 24:38.663
And I think maybe I was dying, too.

24:38.688 --> 24:40.530
I just didn't know it.

24:40.555 --> 24:43.389
But I was broken. [CHUCKLES]

24:43.414 --> 24:45.006
And you were right.

24:45.315 --> 24:48.061
Instead of dealing with that,
I tried to save you.

24:49.022 --> 24:51.506
The way that I couldn't save Jon.

24:51.531 --> 24:53.530
And I know now that I
put way too much pressure

24:53.555 --> 24:54.959
on our relationship.

24:54.984 --> 24:56.959
And I screwed it up.

25:01.067 --> 25:05.348
And I just didn't want today
to go by without saying that.

25:05.942 --> 25:07.709
Thank you.

25:09.016 --> 25:12.092
But it's not all on you, Gary.

25:12.117 --> 25:14.545
Um, cancer wasn't the only problem

25:14.570 --> 25:16.545
I brought to our relationship.

25:18.312 --> 25:20.257
I was broken, too.

25:29.686 --> 25:31.837
[SNIFFS] Well...

25:31.862 --> 25:33.391
[SIGHS]

25:33.416 --> 25:35.321
I'm gonna let you pee now.

25:35.346 --> 25:38.860
After all, you have a tiny bladder.

25:44.117 --> 25:47.095
EDDIE: [VOICE BREAKING] For so long,
I wondered whether or not you knew.

25:47.237 --> 25:49.516
But the thing is, it doesn't matter.

25:51.332 --> 25:52.881
I knew.

25:52.906 --> 25:54.529
I knew what we did.

25:55.152 --> 25:57.118
[SNIFFLES]

25:58.234 --> 26:00.217
And I'm sorry, Jon.

26:04.069 --> 26:06.225
I am so sorry.

26:10.076 --> 26:11.561
I love you, man.

26:16.192 --> 26:17.944
Thank you for this.

26:19.296 --> 26:21.296
He would've been so proud of you.

26:24.471 --> 26:27.420
There's something I think
you might want to hear.

26:27.876 --> 26:29.444
[SNIFFLES]

26:29.469 --> 26:31.047
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

26:31.533 --> 26:33.334
<i>Hey, it's Jon.</i>

26:33.359 --> 26:35.529
<i>I was hoping to speak to you,
not just leave a message,</i>

26:35.554 --> 26:36.983
<i>but, uh...</i>

26:37.405 --> 26:39.975
<i>I just need you to do me a favor.</i>

26:41.563 --> 26:43.444
<i>Love each other.</i>

26:49.319 --> 26:51.519
[SIGHS]

26:53.754 --> 26:55.849
Well, you know...

26:56.163 --> 26:57.474
If that's what he wanted,

26:57.499 --> 27:01.489
then I think he'd be pretty happy.

27:01.708 --> 27:04.375
'Cause that's exactly what we're doing.

27:07.558 --> 27:10.130
♪ The houses caught fire ♪

27:10.395 --> 27:13.292
♪ Caught fire in the fields ♪

27:13.317 --> 27:15.988
♪ And the light was astounding ♪

27:16.253 --> 27:18.964
- ♪ I spent many years ♪
- [INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

27:18.989 --> 27:21.925
- ♪ Many years in the darkness ♪
- Ooh.

27:22.105 --> 27:24.284
Vino? Vino, sir?

27:24.309 --> 27:25.472
Theo, I got you.

27:25.497 --> 27:27.722
♪ ... my best ♪

27:27.747 --> 27:30.471
♪ We all need someone ♪

27:30.496 --> 27:33.064
- ♪ To love and to hold ♪
- [BOTH CHUCKLE]

27:33.471 --> 27:38.721
♪ We all need shelter to
keep us from the cold ♪

27:38.746 --> 27:42.299
- ♪ We all need laughter ♪
- What? We got cookies.

27:42.324 --> 27:44.986
♪ When life gets hard ♪

27:45.011 --> 27:50.197
♪ We all need someone to
love us for who we are ♪

27:50.222 --> 27:55.222
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

28:02.032 --> 28:05.060
♪ We all need shelter ♪

28:05.085 --> 28:07.742
♪ To keep us from the cold ♪

28:07.767 --> 28:13.453
♪ We all need laughter
