♪ We all need someone to
love us for who we are ♪

28:18.666 --> 28:20.422
[GLASS CLINKING]

28:20.447 --> 28:22.375
- What is he doing?
- Is he making a toast?

28:22.844 --> 28:24.805
I'd like to make a toast.

28:25.338 --> 28:28.703
The Egyptians believed
that you die twice...

28:29.450 --> 28:32.096
Once when you take your final breath

28:32.121 --> 28:35.227
and then again the last
time someone says your name.

28:36.243 --> 28:38.154
They believed your spirit lived on

28:38.179 --> 28:40.913
as long as people kept remembering you.

28:42.540 --> 28:46.227
So as long as we always
keep remembering Uncle Jon,

28:46.252 --> 28:48.656
he'll never really be gone.

28:55.019 --> 28:57.098
Was that okay?

28:57.123 --> 28:59.557
That was more than okay, Theo.

29:02.570 --> 29:05.602
That is a tough act to follow,
young man.

29:06.122 --> 29:08.164
But I-I would like to add something.

29:10.165 --> 29:14.320
So much has happened since he passed.

29:16.925 --> 29:18.399
We were lost.

29:19.579 --> 29:21.945
And... And now, it feels

29:21.970 --> 29:26.438
like we're all finally
in a better place.

29:27.427 --> 29:29.086
All of us.

29:29.959 --> 29:32.472
Not because he died.

29:32.653 --> 29:35.498
It's because he convinced us to live.

29:46.017 --> 29:48.017
Let's all raise a glass.

29:52.748 --> 29:53.860
To Jon.

29:53.885 --> 29:55.762
- To Jon.
- To Jon.

29:55.787 --> 29:57.363
- To Jon.
- Jon.

29:57.388 --> 29:59.496
- [GLASSES CLINKING]
- So good.

29:59.521 --> 30:01.074
- [LIQUID POURS]
- ROME: Oh!

30:09.237 --> 30:11.496
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

30:11.801 --> 30:14.090
- Hey.
- Hey.

30:14.115 --> 30:15.622
You okay?

30:15.647 --> 30:17.257
Yeah.

30:17.354 --> 30:19.727
- No. [CHUCKLES]
- [CHUCKLES]

30:19.752 --> 30:22.865
You know, before things
got bad between Jon and me,

30:22.890 --> 30:24.638
there was this one Saturday.

30:24.663 --> 30:28.333
The kids were at camp, and
he had just come up for air

30:28.358 --> 30:30.603
from this big deal that he had closed,

30:30.628 --> 30:33.812
and we were supposed to go out
to a fancy restaurant for dinner.

30:33.837 --> 30:35.711
We ended up staying in.

30:35.736 --> 30:38.742
We just spent the whole night in bed

30:38.767 --> 30:44.282
laughing and talking
and just being together.

30:44.307 --> 30:45.775
[GLASS THUDS]

30:45.800 --> 30:47.798
I miss who we were.

30:47.915 --> 30:49.752
Oh, D.

30:49.777 --> 30:52.756
It's just that with
everything that's happened...

30:52.842 --> 30:56.705
The shock of his death and
my guilt over the affair,

30:56.730 --> 30:58.875
almost losing the house...

30:58.900 --> 31:02.019
The one thing I never got
to do was grieve my husband.

31:02.762 --> 31:04.753
And I know... [LAUGHS]

31:04.778 --> 31:06.550
I know it probably
doesn't make any sense.

31:06.575 --> 31:09.628
Trust me, it makes perfect sense.

31:09.653 --> 31:11.111
I'd give anything to go back

31:11.136 --> 31:13.433
and have a second chance with him.

31:16.851 --> 31:19.220
[LAUGHTER]

31:22.611 --> 31:24.073
D, you still want to do this now?

31:24.098 --> 31:25.480
Yes, let's do it!

31:25.505 --> 31:26.830
- Come.
- Okay, let's go.

31:26.855 --> 31:28.032
Uh... [CLEARS THROAT]

31:28.057 --> 31:29.553
DELILAH: Everybody, come on.

31:29.578 --> 31:32.498
Grab your coats.
We're taking a little road trip.

31:32.523 --> 31:34.544
- Mm-hmm.
- Where are we going?

31:34.569 --> 31:35.968
It's a surprise.

31:38.646 --> 31:40.325
Can I open them yet?

31:40.350 --> 31:42.014
- REGINA: [CHUCKLES]
- GARY: Come on, you guys.

31:42.038 --> 31:43.747
This woman doesn't
need any more surprises.

31:43.772 --> 31:44.916
Okay.

31:44.941 --> 31:46.841
You can open your eyes now.

31:47.580 --> 31:49.005
Ta-da!

31:49.030 --> 31:50.347
[CHUCKLES]

31:50.372 --> 31:52.574
- Where are we?
- We're right above Someday.

31:52.599 --> 31:54.816
It's part of the old
Griffin Street Bakery.

31:54.841 --> 31:57.338
And we've been using it as
storage for the restaurant.

31:57.363 --> 31:58.453
Sure, it needs some TLC,

31:58.478 --> 32:00.789
but because it's part of
the lease Jon negotiated...

32:00.814 --> 32:02.733
The rent's already
being paid by Someday.

32:02.758 --> 32:06.631
So the space is yours,
i-if you want it...

32:06.656 --> 32:08.178
For your new office.

32:11.348 --> 32:12.788
[CHUCKLES]

32:12.813 --> 32:14.600
You can't be serious.

32:15.716 --> 32:18.131
Jon would have wanted you to have this.

32:18.506 --> 32:20.886
You gave me my house.

32:21.011 --> 32:24.030
The least I can do is...
is give you an office.

32:24.055 --> 32:26.150
With your name on the door.

32:27.549 --> 32:29.361
- Wow.
- Mmhmm.

32:29.386 --> 32:31.314
I don't know what to say.

32:31.339 --> 32:34.455
[LAUGHTER]

32:34.480 --> 32:36.580
To be honest, I wasn't sure

32:36.605 --> 32:39.851
I'd ever feel like part
of the group again

32:39.876 --> 32:42.431
after Jon was gone.

32:42.546 --> 32:46.749
He was the one that always
made me feel like I belonged.

32:48.841 --> 32:50.970
Not anymore.

32:50.995 --> 32:55.397
You really are like family to me.

32:59.707 --> 33:02.470
So, thank you.

33:02.495 --> 33:05.047
[CHUCKLES]

33:05.072 --> 33:06.517
You're welcome.

33:06.542 --> 33:08.139
You had nothing to do with this.

33:08.164 --> 33:09.543
That's not true.
I helped with the, uh...

33:09.567 --> 33:11.034
No... No. You didn't.

33:11.059 --> 33:12.770
- No, I didn't.
- Right.

33:12.795 --> 33:14.672
- [LAUGHS]
- To new beginnings!

33:15.109 --> 33:16.203
Hear, hear!

33:16.228 --> 33:17.867
- To new beginnings!
- New beginnings!

33:17.892 --> 33:19.159
... new beginnings!

33:26.813 --> 33:28.873
[BOTH SIGH]

33:29.571 --> 33:32.467
[SNIFFS] That was
a nice toast at dinner.

33:32.492 --> 33:34.162
Oh, yeah.

33:34.455 --> 33:36.709
I've been thinking a lot about that day.

33:36.733 --> 33:38.845
Like what could've
happened if things had gone

33:38.869 --> 33:40.613
maybe just a little bit differently.

33:40.637 --> 33:44.039
Like if... if you hadn't
called me seven times.

33:45.211 --> 33:47.045
Dude, I'd have swallowed those pills.

33:47.070 --> 33:48.848
Nah, I just hit redial.

33:48.873 --> 33:50.678
No, come on, man, I'm being serious.

33:51.561 --> 33:54.326
You never stopped trying to reach me.

33:54.964 --> 33:57.632
You didn't give up.

34:00.615 --> 34:03.444
And I realized, like, "Wow."

34:03.929 --> 34:06.841
No matter how bad you feel,

34:06.866 --> 34:08.795
no matter how hopeless it seems,

34:10.428 --> 34:12.706
it's never too late to start over.

34:14.869 --> 34:16.400
Yeah.

34:16.426 --> 34:19.471
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

34:23.120 --> 34:26.408
I am not supposed to tell you this.

34:28.438 --> 34:30.907
But Maggie's going to Oxford.

34:32.643 --> 34:34.947
She leaves in a week.

34:34.972 --> 34:36.925
[SIGHS]

34:38.522 --> 34:40.010
[SIGHS]

34:42.398 --> 34:44.273
Hey. Maggie.

34:44.596 --> 34:47.049
You're not seriously
sneaking out, are you?

34:47.308 --> 34:49.908
Yeah, I just didn't want
to ruin the moment.

34:50.871 --> 34:52.250
Uh-huh.

34:52.275 --> 34:53.549
What's up?

34:53.574 --> 34:55.174
Nothing.

34:55.958 --> 34:58.972
When we were at Delilah's,

34:59.136 --> 35:02.431
Gary said all of this stuff
to me about our relationship,

35:02.456 --> 35:03.908
and I can't help but feel like

35:03.933 --> 35:06.478
if he had said that when we broke up,

35:06.503 --> 35:08.381
maybe we would still be together.

35:08.406 --> 35:09.978
Well, then why aren't you?

35:10.003 --> 35:11.246
Gina.

35:11.271 --> 35:14.080
We've moved on.
We're in completely different places.

35:16.327 --> 35:18.025
[SIGHS]

35:18.050 --> 35:19.861
No, you're not.

35:20.347 --> 35:22.258
At the restaurant that day, you know,

35:22.283 --> 35:25.142
you said you kind of wished
that wine was from Gary?

35:26.774 --> 35:28.549
Well, it was.

35:28.574 --> 35:29.931
- What?
- Yeah.

35:29.956 --> 35:31.986
Maggie, he's still in love with you.

35:34.940 --> 35:39.197
I can't... I can't even
process that right now.

35:40.796 --> 35:42.353
I'm going to Oxford.

35:42.378 --> 35:44.656
♪ As I walk ♪

35:45.624 --> 35:48.403
♪ This wicked world ♪

35:48.428 --> 35:50.494
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

35:50.519 --> 35:55.705
♪ Searching for light in
the darkness of insanity ♪

35:55.730 --> 35:57.346
You look happy.

35:57.371 --> 35:58.949
Very.

35:58.974 --> 36:01.018
♪ I ask myself ♪

36:01.043 --> 36:04.588
You know, earlier,
when Rome talked about...

36:05.166 --> 36:06.994
how we're all in a better place?

36:07.019 --> 36:08.549
Yeah.

36:08.574 --> 36:10.619
I was thinking about us, too.

36:11.832 --> 36:13.478
Our anniversary is coming up.

36:13.503 --> 36:14.747
I know.

36:14.772 --> 36:16.431
12 years. [CHUCKLES]

36:16.857 --> 36:18.635
I was thinking...

36:19.950 --> 36:23.864
what if we renewed our vows?

36:25.988 --> 36:29.111
♪ What's so funny 'bout peace, love... ♪

36:29.136 --> 36:31.556
Eddie Saville,

36:31.864 --> 36:34.744
will you marry me? Again?

36:34.769 --> 36:37.572
♪ What's so funny 'bout peace, love... ♪

36:37.597 --> 36:40.642
You have no idea how
badly I want to do that.

36:40.667 --> 36:45.900
♪♪

36:45.925 --> 36:48.955
♪ And as I walk on ♪

36:49.820 --> 36:53.713
- ♪ Through troubled times ♪
- [KNOCK ON DOOR]

36:54.551 --> 36:57.306
♪ My spirit gets so... ♪

36:57.331 --> 36:58.971
Dad, what are you doing here?

36:58.996 --> 37:01.041
Brought something over for the baby.

37:01.407 --> 37:02.718
Okay.

37:04.256 --> 37:05.931
And...

37:06.270 --> 37:08.689
I wanted to say...

37:09.596 --> 37:11.603
I'm glad you're here.

37:16.171 --> 37:18.338
Thanks.

37:18.667 --> 37:20.955
♪ Sweet harmony ♪

37:20.980 --> 37:25.955
♪ 'Cause each time
I feel it slippin' away ♪

37:25.980 --> 37:29.439
- ♪ It just makes me wanna cry ♪
- Come on in.

37:29.464 --> 37:30.846
[SIGHS]

37:30.871 --> 37:32.471
♪ What's so funny 'bout ♪

37:32.496 --> 37:36.791
- [SNIFFLES]
- ♪ Peace, love and understanding? ♪

37:37.162 --> 37:39.463
♪ Oooooh ♪

37:39.488 --> 37:44.517
♪ What's so funny 'bout peace,
love and understanding? ♪

37:44.542 --> 37:46.252
Hi.

37:46.444 --> 37:48.222
[CHUCKLES] Yeah.

37:48.379 --> 37:50.924
Uh, look, I know
this is probably the last thing

37:50.949 --> 37:52.947
you were expecting, but...

37:53.524 --> 37:56.783
any chance you want to meet for a drink?

37:56.808 --> 37:58.275
♪ Ooooooh ♪

37:58.300 --> 38:00.697
Need a second just to
get this out of the way.

38:01.152 --> 38:02.486
You ready, Pop?

38:02.994 --> 38:05.002
Ready when you are.

38:07.856 --> 38:09.934
REGINA: Oh. The stars...

38:09.959 --> 38:12.504
Just like the ones you
had when you were a kid.

38:12.529 --> 38:13.640
Hmm.

38:13.665 --> 38:15.150
Thank you.

38:15.175 --> 38:17.939
♪ Sweet harmony, now ♪

38:17.964 --> 38:22.635
♪ 'Cause each time
I feel it slippin' away ♪

38:22.979 --> 38:26.291
♪ It just makes me wanna cry ♪

38:26.316 --> 38:27.744
There you are. [SIGHS]

38:27.769 --> 38:31.080
I, uh, wasn't sure you'd be up for this.

38:31.844 --> 38:34.088
Well, if we're being honest,

38:34.113 --> 38:36.480
I'm a little surprised you reached out.

38:37.390 --> 38:39.502
But I'm glad you did.

38:39.841 --> 38:41.721
So am I.

38:42.236 --> 38:44.767
- What happened with Becky?
- [CHUCKLES]

38:44.792 --> 38:48.138
I realized she was just another rebound.

38:48.440 --> 38:50.814
So, what does that make me?

38:51.189 --> 38:52.967
A fresh start.

38:52.992 --> 38:55.303
♪ Understanding ♪

38:55.328 --> 38:59.096
♪♪

38:59.121 --> 39:02.010
Hey. So, I was thinking maybe...

39:02.035 --> 39:04.228
we do our vows here at home.

39:04.806 --> 39:07.150
I love that idea.

39:14.661 --> 39:17.025
Eddie! There you are.

39:19.727 --> 39:21.369
I'll, uh, be right back.

39:21.394 --> 39:23.272
I got to call my sister.

39:23.297 --> 39:25.998
Okay. Make sure you
invite her to the vows.

39:28.081 --> 39:30.213
[RINGING]

39:30.894 --> 39:33.017
Hey, Lindsay, it's me. Um...

39:33.535 --> 39:35.377
Look, I need to talk.

39:35.402 --> 39:39.361
I had a dream about Alex, and...

39:39.386 --> 39:41.947
I-I need to know what
happened the night she died.

39:43.551 --> 39:44.862
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

39:44.887 --> 39:46.921
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

39:52.335 --> 39:54.681
[SIGHS]

39:55.627 --> 39:57.871
JON: You should answer it, Delilah.

40:00.137 --> 40:02.060
[VIBRATING CONTINUES]

40:02.085 --> 40:04.919
I mean, give the guy a break already.

40:04.944 --> 40:07.005
[CHUCKLES]

40:07.030 --> 40:09.310
I don't want to answer it.

40:10.038 --> 40:11.669
He's not you.

40:11.694 --> 40:13.763
Yeah.

40:15.189 --> 40:17.083
But I wasn't me, either.

40:17.108 --> 40:18.941
Not at the end.

40:20.766 --> 40:22.645
We both know that I broke my vows

40:22.670 --> 40:24.706
long before you broke yours.

40:25.540 --> 40:27.641
I stopped being there for you.

40:29.086 --> 40:30.925
You have to let me go.

40:32.007 --> 40:33.902
If you want to know what I want...

40:35.636 --> 40:37.472
it's for you to be happy.

40:40.980 --> 40:43.092
I miss you so much.

40:48.522 --> 40:49.584
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

40:49.609 --> 40:51.053
SOPHIE: Mom?

41:00.519 --> 41:02.064
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
